ce:section.ce:para:
Next, we tested the J-V curves of perovskite photovoltaic cells (Table 2
                     ), based on GQD SnO2 with doping concentrations of 0%, 1.5%, 3%, 4.5%, and 6% (Fig. 8
                     ). From the J-V curve, we can determine that, when the doping concentration of the GQDs is lower than 4.5%, then the efficiency of the ternary hybrid perovskite photovoltaic cell gradually increases as the concentration of the GQDs increases. When the doping concentration is 0%, then the pristine devices achieve a photoelectric conversion efficiency of 15.52%, and the corresponding JSC is 21.12 mA/cm2. However, under the optimal condition of 4.5%, the data efficiency and short-circuit current are 18.55 mA/cm2 and 21.26 mA/cm2, respectively.This is due to the fact that the SnO2 film optimized by the graphene quantum dots flattens, the roughness and the defect recombination are reduced, the crystallinity of the perovskite surface is improved, and the surface produces ohm contact. At the same time, the conductivity of SnO2 ETL is improved, which in turn improves the transfer of charges and the ability of charge extraction. Finally, the photoelectric performance of the perovskite photovoltaic solar cells is improved. This is consistent with the SEM images of the perovskite surface based on the doped SnO2.
